import { Component } from '@angular/core';
import { ITooltipParams } from '@ag-grid-community/core';
import { ITooltipAngularComp } from '@ag-grid-community/angular';

@Component({
  selector: 'tooltip-component',
  template: ` <div class="custom-tooltip" [style.background-color]="color">
    <p>
      <span>{{ data.athlete }}</span>
    </p>
    <p><span>Country: </span>{{ data.country }}</p>
    <p><span>Total: </span>{{ data.total }}</p>
  </div>`,
  styles: [
    `
      :host {
        position: absolute;
        width: 150px;
        height: 70px;
        pointer-events: none;
        transition: opacity 1s;
      }

      :host.ag-tooltip-hiding {
        opacity: 0;
      }

      .custom-tooltip p {
        margin: 5px;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .custom-tooltip p:first-of-type {
        font-weight: bold;
      }
    `,
  ],
})
export class CustomTooltip implements ITooltipAngularComp {
  private params: { color: string } & ITooltipParams;
  private data: any[];
  private color: string;

  agInit(params: { color: string } & ITooltipParams): void {
    this.params = params;

    this.data = params.api.getDisplayedRowAtIndex(params.rowIndex).data;
    this.color = this.params.color || 'white';
  }
}

import { Component, ViewChild } from '@angular/core';
import { CustomTooltip } from './custom-tooltip.component';


/**
 * Renderer for showing alerts
 */
function alertIndicator(params) {
 
  var icon = document.createElement('i');

  // visually indicate if this months value is higher or lower than last months value

  if (params.value == 'Green') {
    icon.classList.add.apply(icon.classList, [
      'fas',
      'fa-stack-1x',
      'fa-lg',
      'fa-check-circle',
      'text-success'
    ]);
  } else if (params.value == 'Red') {
    icon.classList.add.apply(icon.classList, [
        'fas',
        'fa-stack-1x',
        'fa-lg', 
      'fa-shield-alt',
      'text-danger'
    ]);
  } else if (params.value == 'Blue') {
    icon.classList.add.apply(icon.classList, [
        'fas',
        'fa-stack-1x',
        'fa-lg',
      'fa-shield-alt',
      'text-info'
    ]);
  } else if (params.value == 'Yellow') {
    icon.classList.add.apply(icon.classList, [
        'fas',
        'fa-stack-1x',
        'fa-lg',
      'fa-exclamation-triangle',
      'text-warning'
    ]);
  }

  var element = document.createElement('span');
  element.classList.add('fa-stack');
  element.classList.add('fa-sm');

  element.style.marginLeft = 'auto';
  element.style.marginRight = 'auto';
  element.appendChild(icon);

  return element;
}

/**
 * Renderer for showing links
 */
function linkRenderer(params) {
  var link = document.createElement('a');
  link.onclick = function() {
    alert('You clicked ticket #' +params.value);
  }
  link.innerHTML = params.value;
  return link;
}
 
/**
 * Renderer for showing custom loading messages
 */
function CustomLoadingCellRenderer(params) {
  var loadingMsg = document.createElement('div');
  loadingMsg.innerHTML = '<div class="ag-custom-loading-cell" style="padding-left: 10px; line-height: 25px;"> <i class="fas fa-spinner fa-pulse"></i> <span>LOADING</span></div>  ';
  return loadingMsg;
}

/**
 * Formatter for displaying currency values
 */
function currencyFormatter(params) {
  var numberValue = Math.floor(params.value)
  .toString();
  return "$" + parseFloat(numberValue).toFixed(2).replace(/(\d)(?=(\d{3})+\.)/g, '$1,');
}

      headerName: 'Service Date',
      field: 'service_date',
      headerClass: 'text-center',
      cellClass: 'text-center',
      filter: 'agDateColumnFilter',        
      filterParams: {
          // provide comparator function
          comparator: (filterLocalDateAtMidnight, cellValue) => {
              const dateAsString = cellValue;

              if (dateAsString == null) {
                  return 0;
              }

              // In the example application, dates are stored as dd/mm/yyyy
              // We create a Date object for comparison against the filter date
              const dateParts = dateAsString.split('/');
              const day = Number(dateParts[2]);
              const month = Number(dateParts[1]) - 1;
              const year = Number(dateParts[0]);
              const cellDate = new Date(year, month, day);

              // Now that both parameters are Date objects, we can compare
              if (cellDate < filterLocalDateAtMidnight) {
                  return -1;
              } else if (cellDate > filterLocalDateAtMidnight) {
                  return 1;
              }
              return 0;
          }
        }
    },
